oracle.dmt.jdm.algorithm.glm
Interface OraGLMSettings

All Superinterfaces:
javax.datamining.base.AlgorithmSettings, javax.datamining.supervised.SupervisedAlgorithmSettings
All Known Subinterfaces:
OraGLMClassificationSettings, OraGLMRegressionSettings
public interface OraGLMSettings
extends javax.datamining.supervised.SupervisedAlgorithmSettings

OraGLMSettings is the super interface for GLM classification and regression algorithm settings interface. It defines the common GLM setting, that includes:

  • Ridge regression - Enable ridge regression to build a better model when the input data has correlated attributes (multi-collinearity). By default ridge regression enabling flag is set to null, so that system determines it.
  • Diagnostics Table Name - GLM can produce per case/row diagnostics as part of GLM model building. User can optionally specify diagnostics table name to output per row diagnostics that can be used to validate the model. These diagnostics include various types of residuals, influence measures, and the training data predictions. By default no diagnostics table will be created, user has to explicitely specify the diagnostics table name to create one as a by-product of model build.

    For classification models, the diagnostics table will have the following schema:

    1. CASE_ID - Unique identifier for each row of the model build input table
    2. TARGET_VALUE - A value of the target attribute
    3. TARGET_VALUE_PROB - Probability associated with the target value
    4. HAT - Diagonal value of the hat matrix
    5. WORKING_RESIDUAL - Working residuals
    6. PEARSON_RESIDUAL - Pearson residuals
    7. DEVIANCE_RESIDUAL - Deviance residuals
    8. C - Confidence interval displacement diagnostic
    9. CBAR - Confidence interval displacement diagnostic

    For regression model, diagnostics table will have the following schema:

    1. CASE_ID - Unique identifier for each row of the model build input table
    2. TARGET_VALUE - Actual value of the target
    3. PREDICTED_VALUE - Predicted value of the target
    4. HAT - Diagonal value of the hat matrix
    5. RESIDUAL - Normal residual
    6. STD_ERR_RESIDUAL - Standardized residual
    7. STUDENTIZED_RESIDUAL - Studentized residual
    8. PRED_RES -
    9. COOKS_D - Cooks distance
Since:
OJDM 11.1.0

setMissingValueTreatmentType

public void setMissingValueTreatmentType(java.lang.String treatmentType)
Set the missing value treatment type. There are two types of missing value treatments allowed:
  • Use mean value for numerical attributes and mode value for categorical attributes.
  • Exclude the whole case if any of the model singature attribute values miss in case.

By default mean or mode value settings are used.
